# Import necessary libraries
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming df is your DataFrame and 'ACCT_ID' is the column name

# Number of unique values
num_unique_values = df['ACCT_ID'].nunique()
print("Number of unique ACCT_ID values:", num_unique_values)

# Frequency distribution
acct_id_counts = df['ACCT_ID'].value_counts()
print("Frequency distribution of ACCT_ID:")
print(acct_id_counts)

# Missing values
num_missing_values = df['ACCT_ID'].isnull().sum()
percentage_missing = (num_missing_values / len(df)) * 100
print("Number of missing values in ACCT_ID:", num_missing_values)
print("Percentage of missing values in ACCT_ID:", percentage_missing)

# Data type
data_type = df['ACCT_ID'].dtype
print("Data type of ACCT_ID:", data_type)

# Summary statistics (if applicable)
if data_type in ['int64', 'float64']:
    summary_stats = df['ACCT_ID'].describe()
    print("Summary statistics for ACCT_ID:")
    print(summary_stats)

# Visualization (if applicable)
if num_unique_values <= 10:
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    df['ACCT_ID'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('Frequency Distribution of ACCT_ID')
    plt.xlabel('ACCT_ID')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
elif data_type in ['int64', 'float64']:
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    df['ACCT_ID'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20)
    plt.title('Histogram of ACCT_ID')
    plt.xlabel('ACCT_ID')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.show()
